    Stay in the heart of Mumbai.
Located in Mumbai, 0.7 mi from Girgaum Chowpatty Beach, Hotel Orient Regency features a terrace and views of the city. Among the facilities of this property are a restaurant, a 24-hour front desk and room service, along with free WiFi throughout the property. The accommodations features valet parking, luggage storage space and currency exchange for guests.

The hotel will provide guests with air-conditioned rooms offering a desk, a kettle, a fridge, a safety deposit box, a flat-screen TV and a private bathroom with a shower. At Hotel Orient Regency rooms are equipped with bed linen and towels.

The accommodations offers a continental or buffet breakfast.

Popular points of interest near Hotel Orient Regency include Chor Bazaar, Mohd Ali Road and Girgaon Chowpatty Beach. The nearest airport is Chhatrapati Shivaji International Airport Mumbai Airport, 9.9 mi from the hotel.

Hotel Krishna Palace Residency offers comfortable rooms located a 15-minute drive from commercial centers like Nariman Point and Cuffe Parade. It offers a health club, 2 restaurants and free parking.

Krishna Palace Residency Hotel is 14 mi from Chatrapathi Sivaji International Airport and a 5-minute walk from the local railway station. Dentzz Dental Care (Kemps Corner) is 2789 feet while Worli is 2.5 mi away from the property.

Spacious rooms are fitted with Wi-Fi access and satellite channels. They are equipped with a safe, mini-bar and tea/coffee making facilities. The private bathroom is large enough to accommodate a bathtub, and has a hairdryer and amenities.

A business center is available. The hotel also provides airport shuttle, concierge and laundry services.

Krishna Palace’s multi-cuisine restaurant offers a range of local and international dishes. There is also a vegetarian restaurant that offers Jain dishes.

Krishna Palace’s multi-cuisine restaurant offers a range of local and international dishes. There is also a vegetarian restaurant that offers Jain dishes.

background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Scandic Hotel Malmen</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockholm" title="Stockholm" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Stockholm</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sweden" title="Sweden" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Sweden</a> is located two floors underground.</div></div></div><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">A <b>hotel</b> is an establishment that provides paid <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lodging" title="Lodging" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">lodging</a> on a short-term basis. Facilities provided inside a hotel room may range from a modest-quality mattress in a small room to large suites with bigger, higher-quality beds, a dresser, a refrigerator and other kitchen facilities, upholstered chairs, a flat screen television, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/En-suite" class="mw-redirect" title="En-suite" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">en-suite bathrooms</a>. Small, lower-priced hotels may offer only the most basic guest services and facilities. Larger, higher-priced hotels may provide additional guest facilities such as a swimming pool, business centre (with computers, printers, and other office equipment), childcare, conference and event facilities, tennis or basketball courts, gymnasium, restaurants, day spa, and social function services. Hotel rooms are usually <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_number" title="Room number" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">numbered</a> (or named in some smaller hotels and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bed_and_breakfast" title="Bed and breakfast" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">B&Bs</a>) to allow guests to identify their room. Some boutique, high-end hotels have custom decorated rooms. Some hotels offer meals as part of a room and board arrangement. In <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan" title="Japan" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Japan</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capsule_hotel" title="Capsule hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">capsule hotels</a> provide a tiny room suitable only for sleeping and shared bathroom facilities.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">The precursor to the modern hotel was the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inn" title="Inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">inn</a> of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medieval_Europe" class="mw-redirect" title="Medieval Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">medieval Europe</a>. For a period of about 200 years from the mid-17th century, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coaching_inn" title="Coaching inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coaching inns</a> served as a place for lodging for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coach_(carriage)" title="Coach (carriage)" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coach</a> travelers. Inns began to cater to richer clients in the mid-18th century. One of the first hotels in a modern sense was opened in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exeter" title="Exeter" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Exeter</a> in 1768. Hotels proliferated throughout <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Europe" title="Western Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Western Europe</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America" title="North America" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">North America</a> in the early 19th century, and luxury hotels began to spring up in the later part of the 19th century.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Hotel operations vary in size, function, complexity, and cost. Most hotels and major hospitality companies have set industry standards to classify hotel types. An upscale full-service hotel facility offers <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxury_goods" title="Luxury goods" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">luxury</a> amenities, full-service accommodations, an on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and the highest level of personalized service, such as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concierge" title="Concierge" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">concierge</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_service" title="Room service" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">room service</a>, and clothes pressing staff. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_and_resort_hotels" class="mw-redirect" title="Conference and resort hotels" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Full-service hotels</a> often contain upscale full-service facilities with many full-service accommodations, an on-site full-service <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and a variety of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are smaller independent, non-branded hotels that often contain upscale facilities. Small to medium-sized hotel establishments offer a limited amount of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. Economy hotels are small to medium-sized hotel establishments that offer basic accommodations with little to no services. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extended_stay_hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="Extended stay hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Extended stay hotels</a> are small to medium-sized hotels that offer longer-term full-service accommodations compared to a traditional hotel.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeshare" title="Timeshare" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Timeshare</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destination_clubs" class="mw-redirect" title="Destination clubs" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">destination clubs</a> are a form of property ownership involving ownership of an individual unit of accommodation for seasonal usage. A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motel" title="Motel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">motel</a> is a small-sized low-rise lodging with direct access to individual rooms from the car park. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are typically hotels with a unique environment or intimate setting. A number of hotels have entered the public consciousness through popular culture, such as the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ritz_London_Hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="The Ritz London Hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Ritz Hotel</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London" title="London" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">London</a>. Some hotels are built specifically as destinations in themselves, for example <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casino" title="Casino" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">casinos</a> and holiday <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort" title="Resort" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">resorts</a>.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Most hotel establishments are run by a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_manager" title="General manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">general manager</a> who serves as the head executive (often referred to as the "<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_manager" title="Hotel manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">hotel manager</a>"), department heads who oversee various departments within a hotel (e.g., food service), <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_manager" class="mw-redirect" title="Middle manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">middle managers</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Administration_of_business" class="mw-redirect" title="Administration of business" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">administrative</a> staff, and line-level supervisors. The organizational chart and volume of job positions and hierarchy varies by hotel size, function and class, and is often determined by hotel ownership and managing companies.</p></div></div>

background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Scandic Hotel Malmen</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockholm" title="Stockholm" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Stockholm</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sweden" title="Sweden" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Sweden</a> is located two floors underground.</div></div></div><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">A <b>hotel</b> is an establishment that provides paid <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lodging" title="Lodging" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">lodging</a> on a short-term basis. Facilities provided inside a hotel room may range from a modest-quality mattress in a small room to large suites with bigger, higher-quality beds, a dresser, a refrigerator and other kitchen facilities, upholstered chairs, a flat screen television, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/En-suite" class="mw-redirect" title="En-suite" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">en-suite bathrooms</a>. Small, lower-priced hotels may offer only the most basic guest services and facilities. Larger, higher-priced hotels may provide additional guest facilities such as a swimming pool, business centre (with computers, printers, and other office equipment), childcare, conference and event facilities, tennis or basketball courts, gymnasium, restaurants, day spa, and social function services. Hotel rooms are usually <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_number" title="Room number" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">numbered</a> (or named in some smaller hotels and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bed_and_breakfast" title="Bed and breakfast" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">B&Bs</a>) to allow guests to identify their room. Some boutique, high-end hotels have custom decorated rooms. Some hotels offer meals as part of a room and board arrangement. In <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan" title="Japan" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Japan</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capsule_hotel" title="Capsule hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">capsule hotels</a> provide a tiny room suitable only for sleeping and shared bathroom facilities.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">The precursor to the modern hotel was the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inn" title="Inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">inn</a> of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medieval_Europe" class="mw-redirect" title="Medieval Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">medieval Europe</a>. For a period of about 200 years from the mid-17th century, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coaching_inn" title="Coaching inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coaching inns</a> served as a place for lodging for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coach_(carriage)" title="Coach (carriage)" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coach</a> travelers. Inns began to cater to richer clients in the mid-18th century. One of the first hotels in a modern sense was opened in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exeter" title="Exeter" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Exeter</a> in 1768. Hotels proliferated throughout <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Europe" title="Western Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Western Europe</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America" title="North America" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">North America</a> in the early 19th century, and luxury hotels began to spring up in the later part of the 19th century.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Hotel operations vary in size, function, complexity, and cost. Most hotels and major hospitality companies have set industry standards to classify hotel types. An upscale full-service hotel facility offers <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxury_goods" title="Luxury goods" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">luxury</a> amenities, full-service accommodations, an on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and the highest level of personalized service, such as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concierge" title="Concierge" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">concierge</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_service" title="Room service" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">room service</a>, and clothes pressing staff. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_and_resort_hotels" class="mw-redirect" title="Conference and resort hotels" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Full-service hotels</a> often contain upscale full-service facilities with many full-service accommodations, an on-site full-service <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and a variety of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are smaller independent, non-branded hotels that often contain upscale facilities. Small to medium-sized hotel establishments offer a limited amount of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. Economy hotels are small to medium-sized hotel establishments that offer basic accommodations with little to no services. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extended_stay_hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="Extended stay hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Extended stay hotels</a> are small to medium-sized hotels that offer longer-term full-service accommodations compared to a traditional hotel.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeshare" title="Timeshare" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Timeshare</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destination_clubs" class="mw-redirect" title="Destination clubs" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">destination clubs</a> are a form of property ownership involving ownership of an individual unit of accommodation for seasonal usage. A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motel" title="Motel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">motel</a> is a small-sized low-rise lodging with direct access to individual rooms from the car park. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are typically hotels with a unique environment or intimate setting. A number of hotels have entered the public consciousness through popular culture, such as the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ritz_London_Hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="The Ritz London Hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Ritz Hotel</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London" title="London" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">London</a>. Some hotels are built specifically as destinations in themselves, for example <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casino" title="Casino" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">casinos</a> and holiday <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort" title="Resort" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">resorts</a>.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Most hotel establishments are run by a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_manager" title="General manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">general manager</a> who serves as the head executive (often referred to as the "<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_manager" title="Hotel manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">hotel manager</a>"), department heads who oversee various departments within a hotel (e.g., food service), <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_manager" class="mw-redirect" title="Middle manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">middle managers</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Administration_of_business" class="mw-redirect" title="Administration of business" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">administrative</a> staff, and line-level supervisors. The organizational chart and volume of job positions and hierarchy varies by hotel size, function and class, and is often determined by hotel ownership and managing companies.</p></div></div>

background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Scandic Hotel Malmen</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockholm" title="Stockholm" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Stockholm</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sweden" title="Sweden" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Sweden</a> is located two floors underground.</div></div></div><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">A <b>hotel</b> is an establishment that provides paid <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lodging" title="Lodging" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">lodging</a> on a short-term basis. Facilities provided inside a hotel room may range from a modest-quality mattress in a small room to large suites with bigger, higher-quality beds, a dresser, a refrigerator and other kitchen facilities, upholstered chairs, a flat screen television, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/En-suite" class="mw-redirect" title="En-suite" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">en-suite bathrooms</a>. Small, lower-priced hotels may offer only the most basic guest services and facilities. Larger, higher-priced hotels may provide additional guest facilities such as a swimming pool, business centre (with computers, printers, and other office equipment), childcare, conference and event facilities, tennis or basketball courts, gymnasium, restaurants, day spa, and social function services. Hotel rooms are usually <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_number" title="Room number" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">numbered</a> (or named in some smaller hotels and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bed_and_breakfast" title="Bed and breakfast" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">B&Bs</a>) to allow guests to identify their room. Some boutique, high-end hotels have custom decorated rooms. Some hotels offer meals as part of a room and board arrangement. In <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan" title="Japan" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Japan</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capsule_hotel" title="Capsule hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">capsule hotels</a> provide a tiny room suitable only for sleeping and shared bathroom facilities.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">The precursor to the modern hotel was the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inn" title="Inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">inn</a> of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medieval_Europe" class="mw-redirect" title="Medieval Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">medieval Europe</a>. For a period of about 200 years from the mid-17th century, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coaching_inn" title="Coaching inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coaching inns</a> served as a place for lodging for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coach_(carriage)" title="Coach (carriage)" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coach</a> travelers. Inns began to cater to richer clients in the mid-18th century. One of the first hotels in a modern sense was opened in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exeter" title="Exeter" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Exeter</a> in 1768. Hotels proliferated throughout <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Europe" title="Western Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Western Europe</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America" title="North America" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">North America</a> in the early 19th century, and luxury hotels began to spring up in the later part of the 19th century.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Hotel operations vary in size, function, complexity, and cost. Most hotels and major hospitality companies have set industry standards to classify hotel types. An upscale full-service hotel facility offers <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxury_goods" title="Luxury goods" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">luxury</a> amenities, full-service accommodations, an on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and the highest level of personalized service, such as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concierge" title="Concierge" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">concierge</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_service" title="Room service" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">room service</a>, and clothes pressing staff. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_and_resort_hotels" class="mw-redirect" title="Conference and resort hotels" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Full-service hotels</a> often contain upscale full-service facilities with many full-service accommodations, an on-site full-service <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and a variety of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are smaller independent, non-branded hotels that often contain upscale facilities. Small to medium-sized hotel establishments offer a limited amount of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. Economy hotels are small to medium-sized hotel establishments that offer basic accommodations with little to no services. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extended_stay_hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="Extended stay hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Extended stay hotels</a> are small to medium-sized hotels that offer longer-term full-service accommodations compared to a traditional hotel.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeshare" title="Timeshare" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Timeshare</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destination_clubs" class="mw-redirect" title="Destination clubs" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">destination clubs</a> are a form of property ownership involving ownership of an individual unit of accommodation for seasonal usage. A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motel" title="Motel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">motel</a> is a small-sized low-rise lodging with direct access to individual rooms from the car park. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are typically hotels with a unique environment or intimate setting. A number of hotels have entered the public consciousness through popular culture, such as the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ritz_London_Hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="The Ritz London Hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Ritz Hotel</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London" title="London" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">London</a>. Some hotels are built specifically as destinations in themselves, for example <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casino" title="Casino" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">casinos</a> and holiday <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort" title="Resort" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">resorts</a>.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Most hotel establishments are run by a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_manager" title="General manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">general manager</a> who serves as the head executive (often referred to as the "<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_manager" title="Hotel manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Scandic Hotel Malmen</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockholm" title="Stockholm" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Stockholm</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sweden" title="Sweden" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Sweden</a> is located two floors underground.</div></div></div><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">A <b>hotel</b> is an establishment that provides paid <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lodging" title="Lodging" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">lodging</a> on a short-term basis. Facilities provided inside a hotel room may range from a modest-quality mattress in a small room to large suites with bigger, higher-quality beds, a dresser, a refrigerator and other kitchen facilities, upholstered chairs, a flat screen television, and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/En-suite" class="mw-redirect" title="En-suite" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">en-suite bathrooms</a>. Small, lower-priced hotels may offer only the most basic guest services and facilities. Larger, higher-priced hotels may provide additional guest facilities such as a swimming pool, business centre (with computers, printers, and other office equipment), childcare, conference and event facilities, tennis or basketball courts, gymnasium, restaurants, day spa, and social function services. Hotel rooms are usually <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_number" title="Room number" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">numbered</a> (or named in some smaller hotels and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bed_and_breakfast" title="Bed and breakfast" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">B&Bs</a>) to allow guests to identify their room. Some boutique, high-end hotels have custom decorated rooms. Some hotels offer meals as part of a room and board arrangement. In <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Japan" title="Japan" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Japan</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Capsule_hotel" title="Capsule hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">capsule hotels</a> provide a tiny room suitable only for sleeping and shared bathroom facilities.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">The precursor to the modern hotel was the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inn" title="Inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">inn</a> of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medieval_Europe" class="mw-redirect" title="Medieval Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">medieval Europe</a>. For a period of about 200 years from the mid-17th century, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coaching_inn" title="Coaching inn" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coaching inns</a> served as a place for lodging for <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coach_(carriage)" title="Coach (carriage)" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">coach</a> travelers. Inns began to cater to richer clients in the mid-18th century. One of the first hotels in a modern sense was opened in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exeter" title="Exeter" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Exeter</a> in 1768. Hotels proliferated throughout <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_Europe" title="Western Europe" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Western Europe</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_America" title="North America" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">North America</a> in the early 19th century, and luxury hotels began to spring up in the later part of the 19th century.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Hotel operations vary in size, function, complexity, and cost. Most hotels and major hospitality companies have set industry standards to classify hotel types. An upscale full-service hotel facility offers <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Luxury_goods" title="Luxury goods" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">luxury</a> amenities, full-service accommodations, an on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and the highest level of personalized service, such as a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Concierge" title="Concierge" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">concierge</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Room_service" title="Room service" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">room service</a>, and clothes pressing staff. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conference_and_resort_hotels" class="mw-redirect" title="Conference and resort hotels" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Full-service hotels</a> often contain upscale full-service facilities with many full-service accommodations, an on-site full-service <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Restaurant" title="Restaurant" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">restaurant</a>, and a variety of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are smaller independent, non-branded hotels that often contain upscale facilities. Small to medium-sized hotel establishments offer a limited amount of on-site <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Amenity" title="Amenity" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">amenities</a>. Economy hotels are small to medium-sized hotel establishments that offer basic accommodations with little to no services. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extended_stay_hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="Extended stay hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Extended stay hotels</a> are small to medium-sized hotels that offer longer-term full-service accommodations compared to a traditional hotel.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Timeshare" title="Timeshare" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Timeshare</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Destination_clubs" class="mw-redirect" title="Destination clubs" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">destination clubs</a> are a form of property ownership involving ownership of an individual unit of accommodation for seasonal usage. A <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Motel" title="Motel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">motel</a> is a small-sized low-rise lodging with direct access to individual rooms from the car park. <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boutique_hotel" title="Boutique hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Boutique hotels</a> are typically hotels with a unique environment or intimate setting. A number of hotels have entered the public consciousness through popular culture, such as the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Ritz_London_Hotel" class="mw-redirect" title="The Ritz London Hotel" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">Ritz Hotel</a> in <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/London" title="London" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">London</a>. Some hotels are built specifically as destinations in themselves, for example <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Casino" title="Casino" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">casinos</a> and holiday <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resort" title="Resort" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">resorts</a>.</p><p style="margin: 0.5em 0px;">Most hotel establishments are run by a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_manager" title="General manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">general manager</a> who serves as the head executive (often referred to as the "<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hotel_manager" title="Hotel manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">hotel manager</a>"), department heads who oversee various departments within a hotel (e.g., food service), <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_manager" class="mw-redirect" title="Middle manager" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">middle managers</a>, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Administration_of_business" class="mw-redirect" title="Administration of business" style="color: rgb(6, 69, 173); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;">administrative</a> staff, and line-level supervisors. The organizational chart and volume of job positions and hierarchy varies by hotel size, function and class, and is often determined by hotel ownership and managing companies.</p></div></div>
